-- Ghana Needs $1 Billion Each Year for Climate Change, B&FT Says
-- B y   E k o w   D o n t o h
-- 2012-03-23T09:41:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-23/ghana-needs-1-billion-each-year-for-climate-change-b-ft-says.html
Ghana will need $1 billion annually
to adapt to  climate change , Business and Financial Times
reported, citing Jeremias Blaser, deputy country director of the
United Nations Development Programme.  Desertification, droughts, floods and a decline in fresh
water resources have made the West African nation vulnerable to
climate-change threats, Blaser was cited by the Accra-based
newspaper as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ekow Dontoh in Accra at 
 edontoh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Emily Bowers at 
